unity center, sports bar, and living room.&quot; Or the list of Top 10 reasons to be atheist (&quot;You can be proud you're not Muslim, Orthodox Christian, Catholic, or Jewish, even though you know you are one or more of these things.&quot;, etc. &#10;People aren't as sensitive about it and so much of our culture and identity is tied to religion and religious diversity that you just can't escape it. &#10;Personally, I wouldn't mind having to do witness these other rituals. It's part of sharing. It's why we all commemorate Passover, why they rings the churchbells at the same time as the Islamic all to prayer. It's just... brotherhood and unity, to steal the &quot;communist&quot; ideal. &#10;That would work better, I think, than just not having prayer or exposure to... living examples, like that. In a class, in a book, it's not the same. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1109" language="en" documentId="1871" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Esmira" date="17th March 2011 12:00 AM" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.volconvo.com/forums/showthread.php?t=34286&amp;page=2" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1871" notes="" title="Prayer in Public Schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="81"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="82" end="530"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="531" end="682"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="683" end="959"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="960" end="1109"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55"/></xmi:XMI>